annotation.TEXT: Yep. Knew it. So, what puzzle awaits next?
Yeah, that one was wrong, and reset the room. Hmm...
Whoa. Apparently this area is designed so that if I miss a jump, I'll be quickly pulled back to start, unless I can get out of the water right away.
Goal tape average so far: 1177 / 31 = 37.968 stars each.
Oh, this pipe goes places!
Ah, and what's this? It's a new star coin! This one was not here in the previous version of this hack!
Okay, so I've got a P-switch and a large expanse to the left...
WHOOOOAAAA!!!!!
And there's a Chuck trying to football me from over there. Well, I'd better go over and clobber him quickly with my soft and fluffy mantle!

Ooh, also there's a 3x3 square of coins that wasn't here before, along with the missing star coin! What apparently happened is that both side areas share the same item memory setting, and the coins I collected in the cloudy side area the first time made some coins here disappear.
Nah, just air currents that flow upwards.
That door is wrong.
Aha. Already I see a difference. There was a gap in the coins here the first time around, but this time, this coin line is unbroken!
Old star coin, and... Why not? I'll grab the flower here too.
Goal tape average so far: 1147 / 30 = 38.233 stars each.
Also, bonus game.
So, this is apparently a Charging Chuck inhabited lake/sea...
Hey, why are there fish here?! I thought this was Chuck's place!
Feather, feather, and coin? Huh? Did I miss something here? Maybe a flower block was off screen. Well, pick a door quickly!
Oh, hey! The fifth star coin was hidden off screen there! I thought the odd position of that (not so) hidden coin block seemed suspicious...
Oh, hitting the feather block below the P-switch door makes it impossible to enter that door, so maybe that one is actually correct, somehow? Let me reset the room again and try it.
I could potentially get a stomping combo going here, but I'd rather focus on survival now.
Wheeee!!!
Oh, what? ...Huh... That's interesting...
Not that there was much left to stomp in this area anyway...
Time for more hide-and-seek, I guess. However, the flying blocks aren't very good at hiding. That's odd how the blocks stay in front of the trees that Marina goes behind...
Hmm... Well, there are no other doors that I can see here... Unless maybe there's one across this large pit...
Good thing I did bring the P-switch!
I almost rammed into that Eerie back there, but with all these power ups around, it wouldn't have been a big deal if I got hit.
I just had to check that pipe, didn't I?
...And another cape. Well, you're being quite generous today, game.
Ouch! I got beanballed! Well, so much for the fire flower idea...
"L" still says there's nothing besides death in that pit, but I figured I'd check again anyway. (Note: I'm not going to recheck every single level in this updated version.)
Ah, I can use the springboard to easily reach this star coin (although I could've just spin jumped off of Big Boo).
Ooh, let's take an unnecessarily tricky route to get this star coin!
And I could've sworn I slowed down the footage briefly when I screwed up there... Let me check my WMM project file again...

Umm... I think Orin might want to think about surfacing for air there... (If only such a SM64 hack actually existed... Also, that music was a piece of the water level theme from Super Mario 64, by the way.)
There was a flower, and... yet another cape. But, which door should I enter?
Ow. I just got smacked in the face by a fish...
And that's it for this level. Wow, I didn't hear the "Hurry up!" warning here. That's actually a little surprising.
Well, if the game's gonna be generous with the power ups, I guess so! Alright, now grab that last star coin and scram!
And now to pointlessly hit these coin blocks! Gotta hit 'em all!
Oh, god. Flying cheepos! Once again, I could try for a stomping combo, but I'd much rather get the heck out of here!
I'd better get rid of the football kickers quickly, before the footballs get out of control, especially with all of these blocks that I'll be revealing around here!
Oh, maybe I can actually get a 1♥P combo here this time.
You know what? I'm feeling generous today. I'll let you live since you helped clear out those Chucks there!
Whoa! Okay, that's kind of crazy, but maybe if I scroll the screen just a bit...
Bonus game average so far: 81 / 11 = 7.364 1♥Ps each.
So, vote for either 3-3, 3-6, or 5-2, and that'll determine where I head next time! To be continued...
That unlocks 5-2. Okay, so for next time, you guys can vote on either 5-2...
Huh. Light blue air currents? I guess the light blue ones push you with less force than the dark blue ones.
There's the last star coin, so this has gotta be correct.
Odds are those are ordinary turn blocks, but I've gotta check 'em all!
So, there are these hidden blocks that appear and make a fire-breathing sound when I touch them... Oh, god... I wonder what evil puzzles involving these blocks there will be in the future...
I wonder why I'll need this springboard... Does the screen scroll up here?
Whoa. Did the sound just get all echo-y all of a sudden? Weird...
Looks like the wind is heavily involved with my victory "march" here!
Yeah, I think I'll check out this "FLOWERS LEAD" level now!
Bah! Are these ? blocks really worth it?
And now let's hitch a ride on this winged block!
Oh, hey there Chucks. Looks like the game's starting to get a bit tricky with them.
Nuts. Well it would've been tough to get more than 30 from the ground...
There's my P-switch, along with a bunch of obviously incorrect doors.
Alright, and now we can finally get to those voting results! So, will it be 3-3, 3-A, or 5-1? Let's find out...

Oh, yeah. On my first trip through this level, only one feather appeared near midpoint here, probably due to the sprite limit being reached by the koopas above (which I didn't star-kill the first time).

Well, that was certainly an interesting level, and there was no shortage of power ups, that's for sure! I wonder how long it will take raocow to figure out this level... (I cleared it on my first try with 213 seconds left. Can raocow do better?)
Old star coin...
First, let me reset the room one more time, just in case I need the P-switch...
Yeah, I bet you that the doors under the cape blocks would just have reset the room or something like that.
Alright, so I guess 5-1 is called, "The River Where Wind Blows Up". So, it has exploding wind?
Yep, nothing of importance there.
Hmm... Let's hit the P-switch and check the other blocks if I can.
Whoa. I attempted to carry Buzzy outside again, but he woke up just before I entered the pipe there, and I somehow stomped him without getting hurt.
Goal tape average so far: 1117 / 29 = 38.517 stars each.
Sweet! And now I can just keep doing this...
Whoa! Wasn't expecting to return to the main area that way!
Huh? Where am I? Oh, apparently Marina's playing hide-and-seek behind those trees on the left!
I don't need the mushroom...
Alright, so 3-A it is, then!
Hmm... Actually, this isn't a terrible place to play sports. Much better than inside of a thundercloud or volcano or someplace else crazy!
Huh, but there's a feather above that door, while there's a flower to the left... Oh, you tried to trick me, game! Very clever!
Oh, man. Take that guy out quick, before he floods the area with footballs!
And now, let's enter the ice cave side area first, without going to the cloudy side area...
Old star coin...
...Huh. I guess I somehow completely forgot to change the speed of the bonus game clips like I intended to, so it's my mistake, not WMM's. Oh, well. Not a big deal.
Oh, hey there Chuck. How's it going?
Nuts. Just 30 again. Well, that was a rather tricky setup.
Oh, and it looks like we're doing this again. So, let's find the flower block...
Old star coin...
Well, that's interesting...
More chucks. Good thing my soft and fluffy mantle can easily destroy them!
Also, I really want to check all of these blocks... (Gotta check 'em all!)
*Lightbulb* Oh! Got it. I can use the flying ? block that's over here in order to cross that pit!
That unlocks this ghost house, which is 3-5. Wow, its title is in English? Well, then...

That unlocks 3-6. However, I feel like bucking the trend with the one that came in second in the voting. That's right, I'm going to play 5-1 next! Oh, and I'll play that frantic music that I used last episode while I travel there!
Okay, there's the goal, but let's see if I can get any kind of decent goal tape hit here...
...until I screw it up. D'oh! At least I know that I can get a replacement feather just to the right.

This music is from the Game Boy game Mole Mania. It's called "Heading to Level 8", but it also plays as you're running out of time in the bonus game, and if you tick off Grandpa Mole by talking to him way too much right after recovering your health.
And with this final old star coin, I've collected every star coin in this level!
Okay, and this time, the flower block is right there, but there's no door... I bet I need to find a P-switch to make a hidden door appear.
Old star coin...
Huh. I could've sworn I'd sped up the footage here. Oh, well.

Now, there's another level for me to revisit. 8azaz22 also let me know that apparently, there's a star coin in 3-2 that should've appeared, but didn't, and I think I know why... So, let's head on over to 3-2!
No, so...
There! That looks much better!
A floating signpost? Not for long!
More fish, along with a tricky baseball Chuck. Hmm... Maybe my fire flower will help out here.

Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World. Now, 8azaz22 informed me of an update to this hack that adds a fifth star coin to this level. I've gone and downloaded this update, so let's quickly go through 2-5 again!
Wow, this is very unusual... I didn't hear the "Hurry up!" warning at all today, and none of those levels were autoscrollers!
Also, there's a decent number of fish.
Whoa! That could've gotten a little nutters. However, that koopduder over there was nice enough to help me clear these guys out!
Ooh, a cape and a door. But, wait. There's another door over here...
Oh, wow. Two star coins right next to each other?
Well, the level is called "FLOWERS LEAD", so I think I'll try the door that was under the flower block.
And... there's the last old star coin, to make a total of five! Cool, now I'm outta here!
How about mixing Cirno with Gurren Lagann? "Giga Icicle Drill Breaker -Easy-"?
Oh, hey there Chuck. Oh, hey there Chuck.
Old star coin...
Alright! Now I could try to fry them, but I think I'd rather use my soft and fluffy mantle, which has certainly proven itself far more useful here!
BGM: Hitogata Happa - Extremely Forbidden Play (arranged)
